# Keep `design/mermaid/` in sync

When behavior/structure changes in an area covered below, update the matching file **in the same change** (or right after).

| File | Keep aligned with |
|------|-------------------|
| `architecture.md` | Stack, modules (`cborm`, `cfmigrations`), handlers, services, major folders |
| `request-lifecycle.md` | `Application.cfc` startup, routing, handler actions, services, key views/layouts |
| `data-model.md` | Tables, columns, FKs, indexes, constants; migrations + `models/*.cfc` |
| `class-diagram.md` | Entity properties, relationships, injected constants, `models/constants/` |
| `config-and-datasource.md` | Datasource name, CFConfig, ColdBox module settings, env affecting ORM/migrations/seeding |

No one-off implementation noise — only what a new contributor needs. Long specs: short note + pointer (migration, `Application.cfc`, etc.).
